== OpenMW ==

[[File:Openmw.png|thumb|right|150px|OpenMW [https://openmw.org/media/ more...]]]

OpenMW is a free and opensource reimplementation of the engine that featured Morrowind. It's mainly written in C++, utilizing [http://www.libsdl.org SDL2] and [http://www.openscenegraph.org/ openscenegraph] among other libraries. It's still in beta stage, but is already very playable and has a great developer community with lots of [https://github.com/OpenMW/openmw/graphs/contributors contributors]. It [https://wiki.openmw.org/index.php?title=Mod_installation supports mods] and also comes with it's own [http://downloads.openmw.org/opencs-manual/main.pdf Editor (OpenCS)] to create new games.
You need the original Morrowind Data files. If you haven't installed them yet, you can install them straight via the game launcher (launcher USE flag) which is the officially supported method or by using the {{Package|games-rpg/morrowind-data}} package (this might not work for all morrowind releases out there). View a YouTube demo [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aST2MJd2Tis here].

